Foods That Are Good for Your Liver","abstract":"These foods will keep this vital organ thriving.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/nutrition/7-foods-that-are-good-for-your-liver/ss-AA1aqZAy","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"body":"<p>YOU MIGHT NOT express gratitude for your <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a30116737/liver-drink-too-much/\\">liver</a> (or even think about it) much, but it\xE2\x80\x99s working around the clock for you.</p><p>It's a very impressive <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a39443190/organ-donor-crisis-solution/\\">organ</a>, says <a href=\\"https://profiles.mountsinai.org/meena-b-bansal\\">Meena B. Bansal, M.D</a>., professor of medicine, and director of translational research in liver diseases at the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai. It's the first line of defense for any <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42621421/how-toxic-is-your-body/\\">toxin</a> that may try to make its way into our system.</p><p>The liver is incredibly resistant to injury, and seriously resilient. Did you know your liver <a href=\\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/cells-maintain-repair-liver-identified#:~:text=A%20liver%20can%20regrow%20to,overdoses%2C%20and%20fatty%20liver%20disease.\\">can grow back</a> to a normal size even after up to 90 percent of it has been removed?</p><p>Still, it\xE2\x80\x99s important that you avoid things that hurt your liver such as excess <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a27491762/healthiest-ways-to-drink-alcohol/\\">alcohol</a>, recreational <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42270129/gas-station-dope-tianeptine/\\">drugs</a>, and some <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a19539297/the-top-10-supplements-for-men/\\">dietary supplements</a>, said Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CModeration is the key to everything.\\"</p><p>Ahead, a primer on all the liver\xE2\x80\x99s incredible functions and top foods to eat to support the star organ.</p><h4 class=\\"body-h4\\">What Does the Liver Do?</h4><p>You can consider the liver as the gatekeeper to everything we intake, Bansal says. When you eat food or take medications, all the blood flow from the stomach and intestines is first filtered through the liver which then detoxifies medications, metabolizes carbohydrates, lipids and clears bacterial products that may have escaped the gut.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CIn addition, it makes proteins like clotting factors and maintains healthy blood sugar levels,\xE2\x80\x9D she adds. \xE2\x80\x9CIt produces bile that is needed to help us digest and absorb fats in the small intestine.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>The liver is your body\xE2\x80\x99s \xE2\x80\x9Cmetabolic powerhouse,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://crossfit26.com/\\">Kim Yawitz</a>, R.D., a gym owner in St. Louis, Mo. Everything you ingest passes through this gate. The good stuff, like food is broken down into energy and nutrients, then distributed throughout the body or stored away for later use. The bad stuff, like toxins, are filtered out of the blood to be excreted via urine or stool.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CThe liver is responsible for hundreds of life-sustaining functions, so it\xE2\x80\x99s really important to take good care of it,\xE2\x80\x9D Yawitz says.</p><p>What Makes a Food Good for the Liver?</p><p>There are several things that make foods liver-friendly.</p><p>Bansal says foods that are anti-inflammatory or have antioxidant properties are beneficial to the liver. Foods that are high in fiber and promote a healthy weight are also helpful to the liver.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CHighly processed foods that contain fructose corn-syrup are bad for the liver as they cause the liver cells to make unhealthy lipids (fat). As this fat accumulates, it can cause liver injury and inflammation,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. Basically, the less processed and unadulterated the food you eat, the better. \xE2\x80\x9CThink farm to table.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>As a rule of thumb, Bansal says that foods that you think of as good for your heart are also ones that are good for your liver. Just as the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31334554/\\">Mediterranean Diet</a> is known to support cardiovascular health, so does it for your liver. There is no one food in this diet plan that is driving the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30033779/\\">beneficial effects</a>, but rather it's the combination of its multiple components, says Bansal.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CConceptually an overall diet that is 50 percent fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lentils, legumes; 30 percent healthy fat (think avocados, extra-virgin olive oil); 20 percent lean protein from chicken and fish containing omega-3 fatty acids is considered the best combination,\xE2\x80\x9D she says.</p><p>While there\xE2\x80\x99s no single food that will magically improve liver health, foods high in fiber, healthy fats, and certain antioxidants support optimal liver function. Not surprising\xE2\x80\x94 alcohol and drugs can damage the liver, as can eating too much sugar, salt, and <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">saturated fat</a>.</p><p>Overall, healthy lifestyle choices are healthy liver choices. \xE2\x80\x9CThe <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">best ways to protect your liver</a> are to eat a well-balanced diet, exercise, and maintain a healthy body weight,\xE2\x80\x9D says Yawitz.</p>","image":{"width":2121,"height":1414,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1aroqk.img","attribution":"Klaus Vedfelt - Getty Images","title":"7 Foods That Are Good for Your Liver","caption":"<p>YOU MIGHT NOT express gratitude for your <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a30116737/liver-drink-too-much/\\">liver</a> (or even think about it) much, but it\xE2\x80\x99s working around the clock for you.</p><p>It's a very impressive <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a39443190/organ-donor-crisis-solution/\\">organ</a>, says <a href=\\"https://profiles.mountsinai.org/meena-b-bansal\\">Meena B. Interestingly, scientists do not completely understand what exact components of coffee are conferring the benefit since there are numerous compounds in coffee, but it is thought to be the combination.</p><p>Ideally, you should drink black caffeinated coffee to avoid the excess calories that come from cream and sugar, Bansal says. It's worth noting that decaffeinated coffee does not confer the same benefit as regular coffee, but there is no clear evidence that caffeine is the driver of the benefits. Don't get any ideas, though\xE2\x80\x94caffeine supplements are not going to provide the same effect.</p><p>Not a coffee drinker? Black tea may prove helpful for liver health too, though it might not be to the same effect, Bansal says. \xE2\x80\x9CSo if you have a choice, drink coffee. If you cannot drink coffee then black tea may have some benefit albeit much smaller.\xE2\x80\x9D</p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":800,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1ar2g1.img","attribution":"d3sign - Getty Images","title":"1) Coffee","caption":"<p>Okay, we know it\xE2\x80\x99s technically a beverage, but we\xE2\x80\x99re putting this one first.</p><p>\\"The only food where there is clear <a href=\\"https://bmcpublichealth.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12889-021-10991-7\\">evidence</a> for a <a href=\\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1542356521010570\\">beneficial</a> impact on your liver is coffee,\xE2\x80\x9D says Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CCoffee consumption is associated with improvement in liver enzymes, especially in individuals with risk for liver disease.\\"</p><p>Those with pre-existing liver disease have shown improvements in incidence rates of fibrosis and cirrhosis (scarring of the liver), liver cancer, and overall mortality when given three or more cups of coffee per day, she says. The culinary use of banana peel has not been studied in depth, however, banana peels are commonly consumed in India and the Middle East. The fiber rich peels have a slightly bitter taste and a health-promoting nutritional profile. They are rich in antioxidants, essential vitamins, minerals such as potassium and manganese, and carotenoids like lutein, which all important for human health. The peel has also been shown to have anti-fungal and anti-bacterial properties. These Foods Help, According to Nutrition Experts","abstract":"Diversify your plate with these nutritious picks and say goodbye to post-dinner discomfort. When gas causes your stomach to feel, well, inflated\xE2\x80\x94whether it\xE2\x80\x99s that time of the month or you overindulged at dinner\xE2\x80\x94the last thing you want to do is eat more. But, according to nutrition experts, not all snacks are created equal\xE2\x80\x94there are foods that help with bloating, while others exacerbate the situation. \xE2\x80\x9CBloating can be caused by consuming foods that produce more gas than others, contain a high salt content, eating or drinking too quickly, or consuming carbonated drinks,\xE2\x80\x9D explains Marissa West, ACE-certified personal trainer and nutrition specialist and founder of West Kept Secret. \xE2\x80\x9CIt can also be caused by a lactose intolerance, dairy aversion, or another health condition, such as irritable bowel syndrome or celiac disease.\xE2\x80\x9D Depending on the cause of your bloat, certain foods can help you get relief by reducing inflammation, activating the release of digestive enzymes, or coaxing the bloat through your digestive tract with water and fiber. To avoid bloating in the first place, West recommends treading lightly with wheat, cruciferous vegetables like broccoli and cauliflower, and beans, as they can cause excess gas. Cindy Kasindorf, certified nutritional health counselor and founder of Remedy Organics adds that inflammatory foods like fried foods, processed snacks, and sugar can also trigger bloat because they\xE2\x80\x99re harder to digest. While there is no magic pill for nixing that pesky bloated feeling, there are some foods that can help. Check out the below options and keep them at the ready for the next time discomfort strikes.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/nutrition/feeling-bloated-these-foods-help-according-to-nutrition-experts/ss-AA1aB57X","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"title":"1) Avocado","body":"<p>Haas avocados <a href=\\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3664913/\\">are high in fiber, water, and potassium</a>. Here's how to pick the best low-carb snacks that are still healthy.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/nutrition/11-best-low-carb-snacks/ss-AA1bA5nc","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"title":"11 Best Low-Carb Snacks","body":"<p>There's no doubt that people love to <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/healthy-weight-loss-snacks/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">snack</a>. In fact, over 90% of American adults nibble on at least one snack a day, according to market research published in <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10097271/\\"><em>Nutrients</em></a>. Of course, there's a very good chance that you tend to find yourself grabbing a few snacks throughout the day. That's why 22% of the average diet of adults in the U.S. is made up of snacky foods.\xC2\xA0Data found in <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0031938418301951/\\"><em>Physiology & Behavior</em></a> has also shown that Americans prefer snacks like cookies, crackers, chips, candy, cake, and ice cream, as well as popcorn, nuts, seeds, yogurt, and fruit. Some of these options are obviously healthier than others, with some having more calories and fat, while others are considered <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/low-carb-foods/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">low-carb</a> snacks.</p><p>Why is that a good thing? Well, along with helping you to manage or lose weight, foods that don't contain an abundance of carbs can also reduce the risk of both type 2 diabetes and heart disease, according to the <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.mayoclinic.org/healthy-lifestyle/weight-loss/in-depth/low-carb-diet/art-20045831/\\">Mayo Clinic</a>. Granted, that doesn't mean you should cut out all carbs, as they're an important part of a healthy diet.</p><p>\\"<a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/best-carbs-for-weight-loss/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">Carbohydrates</a> are necessary every day for bodily functioning,\\" \xE2\x80\x8Bsays <strong><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"http://www.eatwelltobewellrd.com/\\">Cheryl Mussatto, MS, RD, LD</a></strong>. \\"All organs of the body require carbs, and the brain has a strong appetite for this nutrient. Here's an interesting fact: Even though the human brain represents only 2% of our body weight, it uses up to 20% of our daily calories, more than any other organ in the body!\\"</p><p>\\"Carbohydrates are the main source of energy our body uses to function and it provides glucose, which is our brain's preferred source of energy,\\" says\xC2\xA0<strong><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"http://www.nataliegillettnutrition.com/\\">Natalie Gillett, MS, RD</a></strong>. On the other hand, she explains, \\"While carbohydrates are necessary for proper functioning, too many carbs can lead to weight gain, blood sugar imbalances, and bloating. So, it's important to enjoy the right kinds of carbs in the right amounts. Low-carb snacks can be a great way to get in just enough carbs for an energy boost without overdoing it.\\"</p><p>When it comes to choosing the best low-carb snack, you'll want to opt for food that pleases your palate. Fortunately, we have a range of choices that have just a few carbs but a fair share of tempting tastes that will surely satisfy your snacky <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/ways-to-stop-carb-cravings/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">cravings</a>.</p><p><strong>RELATED</strong>: <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/high-protein-low-carb-snacks/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">13 High-Protein Low-Carb Snack for Weight Loss</a></p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":879,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AAUnpXW.img","attribution":"\xC2\xA9 Provided by Eat This, Not That!","title":"Women Should Stop Doing This Now, Say Health Experts","caption":"<p><p><span>When it comes to health and wellness, women face a unique set of challenges and concerns. \\"We have many of the same stressors as men: family roles, various personal and professional roles, financial issues,\\" says behavioral therapist </span><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://health.clevelandclinic.org/stress-relief-for-overwhelmed-women/\\"><span>Amy Brodsky, LISW-S</span></a><span>. \\"But in addition to all of that, some stressors apply specifically to women.\\" Here are five things that will wreak havoc on women's health and hormones\xE2\x80\x94and should be avoided. growth?","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/nutrition/ask-an-expert-is-black-tea-good-for-hair-growth/ss-AA1bvv1E","locale":"en-ca","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"body":"<div><h2>Expert opinion from Carl Bender</h2></div><h5>Master of Science: Biochemical and Molecular Nutrition \xC2\xB7 6 years of experience \xC2\xB7 USA</h5><p>There are claims that the caffeine in black tea can reduce the hormone dihydrotestosterone, which causes <a href=\\"https://www.bing.com/search?q=hair loss\\">hair loss</a> and that the antioxidants might promote hair growth. However, there is no evidence that it will help regrow hair. Black tea might increase the rate at which your hair grows by stimulating follicles. Overall, the effects are most likely negligible. My recommendation would be to only drink black tea if you want to, don't add it to your diet because it might improve your hair. There are also claims that you can treat your hair with black tea, but it is unlikely that this is any better for your hair than any other hair product.</p><table><tr><th>What are people curious about?</th></tr><tr><td><a href=\\"https://www.bing.com/search?form=SHPART&q=viviscal hair growth\\">Viviscal hair growth</a></td><td><a href=\\"https://www.bing.com/search?form=SHPART&q=hair growth products\\">Hair growth products</a></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\\"https://www.bing.com/search?form=SHPART&q=best hair growth products\\">Best hair growth products</a></td><td><a href=\\"https://www.bing.com/search?form=SHPART&q=hair growth treatment for men\\">Hair growth treatment for men</a></td></tr></table><p>\xE2\x86\x92 <b><a href=\\"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/ask-professionals/Black Tea?questionid=8tpphh2u&type=nutrition&ocid=feed-health-article\\">See more questions and expert answers related to Black Tea.</a></b></p><p>\xE2\x86\x92 <b><a href=\\"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/food/Black Tea?ocid=feed-health-article\\">Love Black Tea? You\xE2\x80\x99re hungry, and it\xE2\x80\x99s just so convenient to head to the office cafeteria for whatever they have to offer. But if your goal is losing weight, planning healthy lunch ideas for <a href=\\"https://www.prevention.com/weight-loss/diets/g20440614/25-best-weight-loss-tips-ever/\\">weight loss</a> to have at the ready makes the biggest difference in supporting your goals.</p><p>And skipping out on lunch is never an option. \xE2\x80\x9CIt\xE2\x80\x99s unfair to expect our body or brain to perform at their best if we aren\xE2\x80\x99t providing the fuel they need through food,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://streetsmartnutrition.com/about/\\">Cara Harbstreet, M.S., R.D., L.D.</a>, owner of <a href=\\"http://www.streetsmartnutrition.com\\">Street Smart Nutrition</a>. \xE2\x80\x9CSkipping a mid-day meal eliminates a key opportunity to get essential nutrition or food groups that may not show up in other meals or snacks.\xE2\x80\x9D </p><h2>How to build a healthy lunch for weight loss</h2><p>The most important thing to keep in mind when planning your lunches for the week is choosing foods that taste good to you, make you feel good, and keep you satisfied, says <a href=\\"https://beautifuleatsandthings.com/about/\\">Andrea Mathis, M.A., R.D.N., L.D.N.</a>, author of <a href=\\"https://www.amazon.com/Complete-Book-Smoothies-Healthy-Energize-ebook/dp/B091MDL2J5?tag=syndication-20&ascsubtag=%5Bartid%7C2141.g.42100898%5Bsrc%7Cmsn-us\\"><em>The Complete Book of Smoothies</em></a>. Without that, you won\xE2\x80\x99t enjoy or look forward to your meals and you\xE2\x80\x99re more likely to snack throughout the day.Additionally, choose foods that are nutrient-dense and support your health goals, Mathis says. Your plate should include fiber, fat, and protein to promote the feeling of fullness and manage appetite. One of her favorite ingredients to incorporate into meals is avocados, which have heart-healthy fats and fiber to keep you satisfied. <br>And if you\xE2\x80\x99re struggling with planning lunches that help you reach your goals, Mathis encourages setting realistic and sustainable goals for yourself. \xE2\x80\x9CTo help you stay on track, choose meals that are easy to prepare and set aside a time or day to prep your meals,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. what a cocktail is, right? Well, not in 1806 they didn\xE2\x80\x99t. May 13, 1806 was one of the very first times the word cocktail was first defined in print, in response to a reader inquiry to the New York federalist newspaper <em>The Balance and Columbian Repository</em>. They wrote that a \xE2\x80\x9Ccock-tail\xE2\x80\xA6is a stimulating liquor, composed of <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/kitchen-tools/a43510984/our-expert-guide-to-stocking-a-portable-bar/\\">spirits</a> of any kind, sugar, water, and <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/food/a42397151/bitters-soda-dry-january/\\">bitters</a>.\xE2\x80\x9D A bit of a far cry from the cocktails we know and love today, sure, but we had to start somewhere! To commemorate the occasion, World Cocktail Day is now celebrated on May 13 every year. Join us in celebration by being your own bartender and enjoying your mixology with a little bit of history this World Cocktail Day.</p><p>These cocktails all feature ingredients, liquors, and recipes from around the globe (and some from closer to home). Big <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/entertaining/g31903538/best-tequila-brands/\\">tequila</a> fan? Well, not in 1806 they didn\xE2\x80\x99t. May 13, 1806 was one of the very first times the word cocktail was first defined in print, in response to a reader inquiry to the New York federalist newspaper <em>The Balance and Columbian Repository</em>. They wrote that a \xE2\x80\x9Ccock-tail\xE2\x80\xA6is a stimulating liquor, composed of <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/kitchen-tools/a43510984/our-expert-guide-to-stocking-a-portable-bar/\\">spirits</a> of any kind, sugar, water, and <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/food/a42397151/bitters-soda-dry-january/\\">bitters</a>.\xE2\x80\x9D A bit of a far cry from the cocktails we know and love today, sure, but we had to start somewhere! To commemorate the occasion, World Cocktail Day is now celebrated on May 13 every year. Join us in celebration by being your own bartender and enjoying your mixology with a little bit of history this World Cocktail Day.</p><p>These cocktails all feature ingredients, liquors, and recipes from around the globe (and some from closer to home). Big <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/entertaining/g31903538/best-tequila-brands/\\">tequila</a> fan? We bet you\xE2\x80\x99ve had a Mexican <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a20139300/best-classic-margarita-recipe/\\">margarita</a> before, but what about their lesser-known cocktail, the <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a43758194/paloma-cocktail-recipe/\\">Paloma</a>? Love the spiced-sweet flavor of <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/entertaining/g32009640/best-rum-brands/\\">rum</a>? Head to the tropics and try a <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a34099414/painkiller-cocktail-recipe/\\">Painkiller</a>, a <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a38885892/dark-and-stormy-recipe/\\">Dark & Stormy</a>, or a <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a28903015/rum-and-coke-recipe/\\">Cuba Libre</a>. Love an <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/food/a41652646/american-amaro-moment/\\">amaro</a>? Italy\xE2\x80\x99s got you\xE2\x80\x94their <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/recipes/a9535/americano-recipe/\\">Americano</a>, <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a38688424/negroni-recipe/\\">Negroni</a>, or <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a36756262/aperol-spritz-recipe/\\">Aperol Spritz</a> is the perfect combo of bittersweet and refreshing.</p><p>Looking to fully branch out, no matter where your cocktails originated? Try a <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a30121457/cherry-sazerac-recipe/\\">Cherry Sazerac</a>, featuring absinthe, a <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a42831107/midori-sour-recipe/\\">Midori Sour</a>, featuring Japanese Midori, our <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a28637365/apple-pie-moonshine-recipe/\\">Apple Pie Moonshine</a>, featuring grain alcohol, or a <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a32784166/frozen-pimms-cup-recipe/\\">Pimm\xE2\x80\x99s Cup</a>, featuring British Pimm\xE2\x80\x99s liqueur. Red meat is high in saturated fat, which is a pro-inflammatory, meaning it promotes inflammation in the body, and <a href=\\"https://www.bmj.com/content/365/bmj.l2110\\">can cause plaque buildup</a>, which increases risk for heart disease and neurodegenerative diseases (harmful to our heart and brain),\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"http://www.roxanaehsani.com\\">Roxana Ehsani</a>, MS, RD, CSSD, LDN, Registered Dietitian Nutritionist and National Media Spokesperson for the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics. \xE2\x80\x9CProcessed meats like sausage, bacon and deli meats also contain high amounts of sodium, which also isn\xE2\x80\x99t beneficial for our overall health and heart health.\xE2\x80\x9D </p><p>For longer life, she notes it\xE2\x80\x99s best to swap out red meat for leaner cuts of protein such as <a href=\\"https://www.womansday.com/food-recipes/g27767001/chicken-breast-recipes/\\">chicken breast</a>, turkey breast, seafood, beans, lentils, nuts, seeds, tofu and non-fat, or low-fat Greek yogurt and cottage cheese.</p><p>RELATED: <strong><a href=\\"https://www.womansday.com/food-recipes/food-drinks/g2373/vegetarian-recipes/\\">90+ Vegetarian Recipes That Will Make You Want to Eat Meat-Free Forever</a></strong></p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":900,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA120ELr.img","attribution":"Adam Gault - Getty Images","title":"Limit your consumption of red meat.","caption":"<p>Sure, red meat has tons of flavor, but it\xE2\x80\x99s also packed with saturated fats that could be hurting your health. </p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CIt\xE2\x80\x99s recommended to limit your intake of red meat such as beef, lamb, sausage, bacon and other processed meats. When you compare it to the entire world population (which <a href=\\"https://www.un.org/en/development/desa/publications/world-population-prospects-2015-revision.html\\">was 7.3 billion</a> in 2015,) it puts into perspective just how rare it is to reach triple digits in age. </p><p>But it\xE2\x80\x99s not impossible, and the numbers are continuing to grow. Foods That Are Good for Your Liver","abstract":"These foods will keep this vital organ thriving.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/nutrition/7-foods-that-are-good-for-your-liver/ss-AA1aqZAy","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"body":"<p>YOU MIGHT NOT express gratitude for your <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a30116737/liver-drink-too-much/\\">liver</a> (or even think about it) much, but it\xE2\x80\x99s working around the clock for you.</p><p>It's a very impressive <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a39443190/organ-donor-crisis-solution/\\">organ</a>, says <a href=\\"https://profiles.mountsinai.org/meena-b-bansal\\">Meena B. Bansal, M.D</a>., professor of medicine, and director of translational research in liver diseases at the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai. It's the first line of defense for any <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42621421/how-toxic-is-your-body/\\">toxin</a> that may try to make its way into our system.</p><p>The liver is incredibly resistant to injury, and seriously resilient. Did you know your liver <a href=\\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/cells-maintain-repair-liver-identified#:~:text=A%20liver%20can%20regrow%20to,overdoses%2C%20and%20fatty%20liver%20disease.\\">can grow back</a> to a normal size even after up to 90 percent of it has been removed?</p><p>Still, it\xE2\x80\x99s important that you avoid things that hurt your liver such as excess <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a27491762/healthiest-ways-to-drink-alcohol/\\">alcohol</a>, recreational <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42270129/gas-station-dope-tianeptine/\\">drugs</a>, and some <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a19539297/the-top-10-supplements-for-men/\\">dietary supplements</a>, said Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CModeration is the key to everything.\\"</p><p>Ahead, a primer on all the liver\xE2\x80\x99s incredible functions and top foods to eat to support the star organ.</p><h4 class=\\"body-h4\\">What Does the Liver Do?</h4><p>You can consider the liver as the gatekeeper to everything we intake, Bansal says. When you eat food or take medications, all the blood flow from the stomach and intestines is first filtered through the liver which then detoxifies medications, metabolizes carbohydrates, lipids and clears bacterial products that may have escaped the gut.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CIn addition, it makes proteins like clotting factors and maintains healthy blood sugar levels,\xE2\x80\x9D she adds. \xE2\x80\x9CIt produces bile that is needed to help us digest and absorb fats in the small intestine.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>The liver is your body\xE2\x80\x99s \xE2\x80\x9Cmetabolic powerhouse,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://crossfit26.com/\\">Kim Yawitz</a>, R.D., a gym owner in St. Louis, Mo. Everything you ingest passes through this gate. The good stuff, like food is broken down into energy and nutrients, then distributed throughout the body or stored away for later use. The bad stuff, like toxins, are filtered out of the blood to be excreted via urine or stool.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CThe liver is responsible for hundreds of life-sustaining functions, so it\xE2\x80\x99s really important to take good care of it,\xE2\x80\x9D Yawitz says.</p><p>What Makes a Food Good for the Liver?</p><p>There are several things that make foods liver-friendly.</p><p>Bansal says foods that are anti-inflammatory or have antioxidant properties are beneficial to the liver. Foods that are high in fiber and promote a healthy weight are also helpful to the liver.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CHighly processed foods that contain fructose corn-syrup are bad for the liver as they cause the liver cells to make unhealthy lipids (fat). As this fat accumulates, it can cause liver injury and inflammation,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. Basically, the less processed and unadulterated the food you eat, the better. \xE2\x80\x9CThink farm to table.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>As a rule of thumb, Bansal says that foods that you think of as good for your heart are also ones that are good for your liver. Just as the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31334554/\\">Mediterranean Diet</a> is known to support cardiovascular health, so does it for your liver. There is no one food in this diet plan that is driving the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30033779/\\">beneficial effects</a>, but rather it's the combination of its multiple components, says Bansal.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CConceptually an overall diet that is 50 percent fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lentils, legumes; 30 percent healthy fat (think avocados, extra-virgin olive oil); 20 percent lean protein from chicken and fish containing omega-3 fatty acids is considered the best combination,\xE2\x80\x9D she says.</p><p>While there\xE2\x80\x99s no single food that will magically improve liver health, foods high in fiber, healthy fats, and certain antioxidants support optimal liver function. Not surprising\xE2\x80\x94 alcohol and drugs can damage the liver, as can eating too much sugar, salt, and <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">saturated fat</a>.</p><p>Overall, healthy lifestyle choices are healthy liver choices. \xE2\x80\x9CThe <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">best ways to protect your liver</a> are to eat a well-balanced diet, exercise, and maintain a healthy body weight,\xE2\x80\x9D says Yawitz.</p>","image":{"width":2121,"height":1414,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1aroqk.img","attribution":"Klaus Vedfelt - Getty Images","title":"7 Foods That Are Good for Your Liver","caption":"<p>YOU MIGHT NOT express gratitude for your <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a30116737/liver-drink-too-much/\\">liver</a> (or even think about it) much, but it\xE2\x80\x99s working around the clock for you.</p><p>It's a very impressive <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a39443190/organ-donor-crisis-solution/\\">organ</a>, says <a href=\\"https://profiles.mountsinai.org/meena-b-bansal\\">Meena B. Bansal, M.D</a>., professor of medicine, and director of translational research in liver diseases at the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai. It's the first line of defense for any <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42621421/how-toxic-is-your-body/\\">toxin</a> that may try to make its way into our system.</p><p>The liver is incredibly resistant to injury, and seriously resilient. Did you know your liver <a href=\\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/cells-maintain-repair-liver-identified#:~:text=A%20liver%20can%20regrow%20to,overdoses%2C%20and%20fatty%20liver%20disease.\\">can grow back</a> to a normal size even after up to 90 percent of it has been removed?</p><p>Still, it\xE2\x80\x99s important that you avoid things that hurt your liver such as excess <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a27491762/healthiest-ways-to-drink-alcohol/\\">alcohol</a>, recreational <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42270129/gas-station-dope-tianeptine/\\">drugs</a>, and some <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a19539297/the-top-10-supplements-for-men/\\">dietary supplements</a>, said Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CModeration is the key to everything.\\"</p><p>Ahead, a primer on all the liver\xE2\x80\x99s incredible functions and top foods to eat to support the star organ.</p><h4 class=\\"body-h4\\">What Does the Liver Do?</h4><p>You can consider the liver as the gatekeeper to everything we intake, Bansal says. When you eat food or take medications, all the blood flow from the stomach and intestines is first filtered through the liver which then detoxifies medications, metabolizes carbohydrates, lipids and clears bacterial products that may have escaped the gut.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CIn addition, it makes proteins like clotting factors and maintains healthy blood sugar levels,\xE2\x80\x9D she adds. \xE2\x80\x9CIt produces bile that is needed to help us digest and absorb fats in the small intestine.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>The liver is your body\xE2\x80\x99s \xE2\x80\x9Cmetabolic powerhouse,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://crossfit26.com/\\">Kim Yawitz</a>, R.D., a gym owner in St. Louis, Mo. Everything you ingest passes through this gate. The good stuff, like food is broken down into energy and nutrients, then distributed throughout the body or stored away for later use. The bad stuff, like toxins, are filtered out of the blood to be excreted via urine or stool.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CThe liver is responsible for hundreds of life-sustaining functions, so it\xE2\x80\x99s really important to take good care of it,\xE2\x80\x9D Yawitz says.</p><p>What Makes a Food Good for the Liver?</p><p>There are several things that make foods liver-friendly.</p><p>Bansal says foods that are anti-inflammatory or have antioxidant properties are beneficial to the liver. Foods that are high in fiber and promote a healthy weight are also helpful to the liver.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CHighly processed foods that contain fructose corn-syrup are bad for the liver as they cause the liver cells to make unhealthy lipids (fat). As this fat accumulates, it can cause liver injury and inflammation,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. Basically, the less processed and unadulterated the food you eat, the better. \xE2\x80\x9CThink farm to table.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>As a rule of thumb, Bansal says that foods that you think of as good for your heart are also ones that are good for your liver. Just as the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31334554/\\">Mediterranean Diet</a> is known to support cardiovascular health, so does it for your liver. There is no one food in this diet plan that is driving the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30033779/\\">beneficial effects</a>, but rather it's the combination of its multiple components, says Bansal.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CConceptually an overall diet that is 50 percent fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lentils, legumes; 30 percent healthy fat (think avocados, extra-virgin olive oil); 20 percent lean protein from chicken and fish containing omega-3 fatty acids is considered the best combination,\xE2\x80\x9D she says.</p><p>While there\xE2\x80\x99s no single food that will magically improve liver health, foods high in fiber, healthy fats, and certain antioxidants support optimal liver function. Not surprising\xE2\x80\x94 alcohol and drugs can damage the liver, as can eating too much sugar, salt, and <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">saturated fat</a>.</p><p>Overall, healthy lifestyle choices are healthy liver choices. \xE2\x80\x9CThe <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">best ways to protect your liver</a> are to eat a well-balanced diet, exercise, and maintain a healthy body weight,\xE2\x80\x9D says Yawitz.</p>","source":"msn"}},{"title":"1) Coffee","body":"<p>Okay, we know it\xE2\x80\x99s technically a beverage, but we\xE2\x80\x99re putting this one first.</p><p>\\"The only food where there is clear <a href=\\"https://bmcpublichealth.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12889-021-10991-7\\">evidence</a> for a <a href=\\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1542356521010570\\">beneficial</a> impact on your liver is coffee,\xE2\x80\x9D says Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CCoffee consumption is associated with improvement in liver enzymes, especially in individuals with risk for liver disease.\\"</p><p>Those with pre-existing liver disease have shown improvements in incidence rates of fibrosis and cirrhosis (scarring of the liver), liver cancer, and overall mortality when given three or more cups of coffee per day, she says. Interestingly, scientists do not completely understand what exact components of coffee are conferring the benefit since there are numerous compounds in coffee, but it is thought to be the combination.</p><p>Ideally, you should drink black caffeinated coffee to avoid the excess calories that come from cream and sugar, Bansal says. It's worth noting that decaffeinated coffee does not confer the same benefit as regular coffee, but there is no clear evidence that caffeine is the driver of the benefits. Don't get any ideas, though\xE2\x80\x94caffeine supplements are not going to provide the same effect.</p><p>Not a coffee drinker? Black tea may prove helpful for liver health too, though it might not be to the same effect, Bansal says. \xE2\x80\x9CSo if you have a choice, drink coffee. If you cannot drink coffee then black tea may have some benefit albeit much smaller.\xE2\x80\x9D</p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":800,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1ar2g1.img","attribution":"d3sign - Getty Images","title":"1) Coffee","caption":"<p>Okay, we know it\xE2\x80\x99s technically a beverage, but we\xE2\x80\x99re putting this one first.</p><p>\\"The only food where there is clear <a href=\\"https://bmcpublichealth.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12889-021-10991-7\\">evidence</a> for a <a href=\\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1542356521010570\\">beneficial</a> impact on your liver is coffee,\xE2\x80\x9D says Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CCoffee consumption is associated with improvement in liver enzymes, especially in individuals with risk for liver disease.\\"</p><p>Those with pre-existing liver disease have shown improvements in incidence rates of fibrosis and cirrhosis (scarring of the liver), liver cancer, and overall mortality when given three or more cups of coffee per day, she says. It's about straight-up, straight-out-of-the ground vegetables.</p><p>And, second, for the purposes of creating a diverse group of plant-based options for you to choose from on this list, legumes are considered a vegetable. So, essentially, not a bag of stale chips.</p><p>Champion recommends thinking of snacks as mini meals. \\"Snacks can be a wonderful time to fill up on nutrients like whole grains, fruits and vegetables,\\" she says. Bananas have a high potassium level, with each medium fruit providing 422 mg. The peel provides an additional 78 milligrams of potassium as well as plenty of fiber. Banana peels are high in polyphenols, carotenoids, and other antioxidants that help your body fight cancer-causing free radicals. Eating more banana peels, particularly green, unripe peels, can boost your antioxidant levels and possibly lower your cancer risk.</p><table><tr><th>What are people curious about?</th></tr><tr><td><a href=\\"https://www.bing.com/search?form=SHPART&q=mediterranean diet\\">Mediterranean diet</a></td><td><a href=\\"https://www.bing.com/search?form=SHPART&q=keto diet\\">Keto diet</a></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\\"https://www.bing.com/search?form=SHPART&q=diabetic diet\\">Diabetic diet</a></td><td><a href=\\"https://www.bing.com/search?form=SHPART&q=weight loss\\">Weight loss</a></td></tr></table><p>\xE2\x86\x92 <b><a href=\\"https://www.msn.com/en-us/health/ask-professionals/Banana?questionid=1lqh04wi&type=nutrition&ocid=feed-health-article\\">See more questions and expert answers related to Banana.</a></b></p><p>\xE2\x86\x92 <b><a href=\\"https://www.msn.com/en-us/health/food/Banana?ocid=feed-health-article\\">Love Banana? The culinary use of banana peel has not been studied in depth, however, banana peels are commonly consumed in India and the Middle East. The fiber rich peels have a slightly bitter taste and a health-promoting nutritional profile. They are rich in antioxidants, essential vitamins, minerals such as potassium and manganese, and carotenoids like lutein, which all important for human health. The peel has also been shown to have anti-fungal and anti-bacterial properties. If planning to eat the peel, those concerned about ingesting pesticides should purchase organically grown bananas.</p><p>\xE2\x86\x92 <b><a href=\\"https://www.msn.com/en-us/health/ask-professionals/Banana?questionid=1lqh04wi&type=nutrition&ocid=feed-health-article\\">See more questions and expert answers related to Banana.</a></b></p><p>\xE2\x86\x92 <b><a href=\\"https://www.msn.com/en-us/health/food/Banana?ocid=feed-health-article\\">Love Banana? Here's how to pick the best low-carb snacks that are still healthy.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/nutrition/11-best-low-carb-snacks/ss-AA1bA5nc","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"title":"11 Best Low-Carb Snacks","body":"<p>There's no doubt that people love to <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/healthy-weight-loss-snacks/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">snack</a>. In fact, over 90% of American adults nibble on at least one snack a day, according to market research published in <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10097271/\\"><em>Nutrients</em></a>. Of course, there's a very good chance that you tend to find yourself grabbing a few snacks throughout the day. That's why 22% of the average diet of adults in the U.S. is made up of snacky foods.\xC2\xA0Data found in <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0031938418301951/\\"><em>Physiology & Behavior</em></a> has also shown that Americans prefer snacks like cookies, crackers, chips, candy, cake, and ice cream, as well as popcorn, nuts, seeds, yogurt, and fruit. Some of these options are obviously healthier than others, with some having more calories and fat, while others are considered <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/low-carb-foods/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">low-carb</a> snacks.</p><p>Why is that a good thing? Well, along with helping you to manage or lose weight, foods that don't contain an abundance of carbs can also reduce the risk of both type 2 diabetes and heart disease, according to the <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.mayoclinic.org/healthy-lifestyle/weight-loss/in-depth/low-carb-diet/art-20045831/\\">Mayo Clinic</a>. Granted, that doesn't mean you should cut out all carbs, as they're an important part of a healthy diet.</p><p>\\"<a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/best-carbs-for-weight-loss/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">Carbohydrates</a> are necessary every day for bodily functioning,\\" \xE2\x80\x8Bsays <strong><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"http://www.eatwelltobewellrd.com/\\">Cheryl Mussatto, MS, RD, LD</a></strong>. \\"All organs of the body require carbs, and the brain has a strong appetite for this nutrient. Here's an interesting fact: Even though the human brain represents only 2% of our body weight, it uses up to 20% of our daily calories, more than any other organ in the body!\\"</p><p>\\"Carbohydrates are the main source of energy our body uses to function and it provides glucose, which is our brain's preferred source of energy,\\" says\xC2\xA0<strong><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"http://www.nataliegillettnutrition.com/\\">Natalie Gillett, MS, RD</a></strong>. On the other hand, she explains, \\"While carbohydrates are necessary for proper functioning, too many carbs can lead to weight gain, blood sugar imbalances, and bloating. So, it's important to enjoy the right kinds of carbs in the right amounts. Low-carb snacks can be a great way to get in just enough carbs for an energy boost without overdoing it.\\"</p><p>When it comes to choosing the best low-carb snack, you'll want to opt for food that pleases your palate. Fortunately, we have a range of choices that have just a few carbs but a fair share of tempting tastes that will surely satisfy your snacky <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/ways-to-stop-carb-cravings/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">cravings</a>.</p><p><strong>RELATED</strong>: <a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://www.eatthis.com/high-protein-low-carb-snacks/?utm_source=msn&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=msn-feed\\">13 High-Protein Low-Carb Snack for Weight Loss</a></p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":879,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AAUnpXW.img","attribution":"\xC2\xA9 Provided by Eat This, Not That!","title":"Women Should Stop Doing This Now, Say Health Experts","caption":"<p><p><span>When it comes to health and wellness, women face a unique set of challenges and concerns. \\"We have many of the same stressors as men: family roles, various personal and professional roles, financial issues,\\" says behavioral therapist </span><a rel=\\"noopener noreferrer external nofollow\\" href=\\"https://health.clevelandclinic.org/stress-relief-for-overwhelmed-women/\\"><span>Amy Brodsky, LISW-S</span></a><span>. \\"But in addition to all of that, some stressors apply specifically to women.\\" Here are five things that will wreak havoc on women's health and hormones\xE2\x80\x94and should be avoided.
